mods.abstract: DETAINED in the jail of the parish of St. John the Baptist the negro boy GEORGES; he says he belongs to Mr. John McCutcheon of the parish of Plaquemines, below the City, has been gone for about six months, meaures 5 feet 4 inches, appears to be about 30 years, speaks english only. The owner is hereby duly notified to claim his property according to law. Parish of St John the Baptist, November 25th 1859. URSIN JACOB, Sheriff.
